AC   P33532; O13866;
Vitamin B6 transporter bsu1 (Vitamin B6 uptake protein 1) (Changed
amiloride resistance protein 1) (Amiloride transporter car1).
"The amiloride resistance gene, car1, of Schizosaccharomyces pombe.";
"The genome sequence of Schizosaccharomyces pombe.";
"Amiloride uptake and toxicity in fission yeast are caused by the
pyridoxine transporter encoded by bsu1+ (car1+).";
-!- FUNCTION: Thiamine-regulated, high affinity import carrier of
    pyridoxine, pyridoxal and pyridoxamine. Also imports, but does not
    export, amiloride and so confers sensitivity.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Membrane; multi-pass membrane protein.
    Note=During mitosis, localizes also to the septum.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the major facilitator superfamily. CAR1
    family.
